We know that, $v_{\text {rms }}=\sqrt{\dfrac{3 R T}{M}}$<br>In the given problem, $\nu_{\mathrm{rms}}$ and $R$ are constants.<br>$\frac{T}{M} = {\rm{ constant}}$<br>$\frac{{{T_H}}}{{{M_H}}} = \frac{{{T_O}}}{{{M_O}}}$<br>$\left[ \begin{array}{l}
\therefore {M_H} = 2,{M_O} = 32\\
{{\dot T}_O} = 47^\circ {\rm{C}} = 320\,{\rm{K}}
\end{array} \right]$<br>$ \Rightarrow \frac{{{T_H}}}{2} = \frac{{273 + 47}}{{32}}$<br>$ \Rightarrow \frac{T}{2} = \frac{{320}}{{32}} = 10$<br>$\therefore T = 20\,{\rm{K}}$

Relation between adiabatic constant $(\gamma)$ and degrees of freedom $(f)$ is given by<br>$\gamma=1+\dfrac{2}{f}$<br>$\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}
  \begin{gathered}
  \therefore \quad {\gamma _1} = 1 + \frac{2}{5} = \frac{7}{5} \hfill \\
  \quad \,\,\,{\gamma _1} = 1.4 \hfill \\ 
\end{gathered} &{\left\{ \begin{gathered}
  \left( {\because \,\,\,f = 5} \right) \hfill \\
  \left( {\because \,\,\,f = 3 + 2 + 0} \right) \hfill \\ 
\end{gathered}  \right\}} 
\end{array}$<br>$\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}
  \begin{gathered}
  \therefore \quad {\gamma _2} = 1 + \frac{2}{6} = \frac{8}{6} \hfill \\
  \quad \,\,\,{\gamma _2} = 1.14 \hfill \\ 
\end{gathered} &{\left\{ \begin{gathered}
  \left( {\because \,\,\,f = 7} \right) \hfill \\
  \left( {\because \,\,\,f = 3 + 2 + 2} \right) \hfill \\ 
\end{gathered}  \right\}} 
\end{array}$<br>Therefore, $\gamma_{1}>\gamma_{2}$<br>So, correct option is (1).
